pokedexEntries.red: Puts enemies to sleep then eats their dreams. Occasionally gets sick from eating bad dreams.
pokedexEntries.blue: Puts enemies to sleep then eats their dreams. Occasionally gets sick from eating bad dreams.
pokedexEntries.yellow: If you sleep by it all the time, it will sometimes show you dreams it has eaten in the past.
pokedexEntries.gold: If you think that you had a good dream, but you can't remember it, a Drowzee has probably eaten it.
pokedexEntries.silver: It remembers every dream it eats. It rarely eats the dreams of adults because children's are much tastier.
pokedexEntries.crystal: When it twitches its nose, it can tell where someone is sleeping and what that person is dreaming about.
pokedexEntries.ruby: If your nose becomes itchy while you are sleeping, it's a sure sign that one of these Pokémon is standing above your pillow and trying to eat your dream through your nostrils.
pokedexEntries.sapphire: If your nose becomes itchy while you are sleeping, it's a sure sign that one of these Pokémon is standing above your pillow and trying to eat your dream through your nostrils.
pokedexEntries.emerald: If your nose becomes itchy while you are sleeping, it's a sure sign that a Drowzee is standing above your pillow and trying to eat your dream through your nostrils.
pokedexEntries.fireRed: A descendant of the legendary animal baku, which is said to eat dreams. It is skilled at hypnotism.
pokedexEntries.leafGreen: Puts enemies to sleep, then eats their dreams. Occasionally gets sick from eating bad dreams.
pokedexEntries.diamond: It can tell what people are dreaming by sniffing with its big nose. It loves fun dreams.
pokedexEntries.pearl: It can tell what people are dreaming by sniffing with its big nose. It loves fun dreams.
pokedexEntries.platinum: It can tell what people are dreaming by sniffing with its big nose. It loves fun dreams.
pokedexEntries.heartGold: If you think that you had a good dream, but you can't remember it, a Drowzee has probably eaten it.
pokedexEntries.soulSilver: It remembers every dream it eats. It rarely eats the dreams of adults because children's are much tastier.
pokedexEntries.black: It can tell what people are dreaming by sniffing with its big nose. It loves fun dreams.
pokedexEntries.white: It can tell what people are dreaming by sniffing with its big nose. It loves fun dreams.
pokedexEntries.black2: It can tell what people are dreaming by sniffing with its big nose. It loves fun dreams.
pokedexEntries.white2: It can tell what people are dreaming by sniffing with its big nose. It loves fun dreams.
pokedexEntries.x: Puts enemies to sleep, then eats their dreams. Occasionally gets sick from eating only bad dreams.
pokedexEntries.y: If you think that you had a good dream but you can't remember it, a Drowzee has probably eaten it.
pokedexEntries.omegaRuby: If your nose becomes itchy while you are sleeping, it's a sure sign that one of these Pokémon is standing above your pillow and trying to eat you dream through your nostrils.
pokedexEntries.alphaSapphire: If your nose becomes itchy while you are sleeping, it's a sure sign that one of these Pokémon is standing above your pillow and trying to eat you dream through your nostrils.
pokedexEntries.sun: A Pokémon that nourishes itself by eating dreams, it is thought to share common ancestry with Munna and Musharna.
pokedexEntries.moon: It finds really fun dreams tasty. When it makes friends with people, it may show them the most delicious dreams it's ever eaten.
pokedexEntries.ultraSun: It can be spotted near recreational facilities, intending to eat the pleasant dreams of children who enjoyed themselves there that day.
pokedexEntries.ultraMoon: It puts its prey to sleep and devours their dreams. It seems that bad dreams taste sour, so Drowzee doesn’t particularly like eating them.
